Yield-Per-Recruit

Source: R/ypr.R
ypr.Rd

Yield-Per-Recruit

ypr(tmax = 20L, k = 0.15, Linf = 100, t0 = 0, a = 1e-05, b = 3,
  Lm = Linf/2, fa = 1, fb = 1, Rt = 1L, nu = 0.2, Lv = Linf/2,
  Llo = 0, Lup = Linf, mu = 0.1, rho = 0, eta = 0.1)

Arguments

tmax

The maximum age.
k

The growth coefficient.
Linf

The mean maximum length.
t0

The age at length 0.
a

The condition factor.
b

The scaling exponent.
Lm

The length at maturity.
fa

The fecundity factor.
fb

The fecundity scaling exponent.
Rt

A count of the recruitment age for the stock recruitment relationship.
nu

The annual probability of dying due to natural causes.
Lv

The length at which vulnerable to harvest.
Llo

The lower harvest length.
Lup

The upper harvest length.
mu

The annual probability of being captured.
rho

The release probability.
eta

The hooking mortality probability.
